                             @{b}@{u} PLAYING THE GAME @{ub}@{uu}



     The game is your standard platformer kinda thing.Use a joystick
     in port 2 to move Charly around,and the fire button to fire the
     relevant weapon.
     Notice that only some weapons can be shot while jumping,and other
     while walking (see @{"Weapons" link "weapons"}).

     At any time press ESC to lose a life,P to pause/unpause and CTRL + C
     to quit and return to WB.You can also control Charly with the cursor
     keys,and shoot with right shift.
     Other key that you will have to use is SPACE.Presssed while in front
     of a warning sign,it will reveal clues,etc.Also,there is a level in
     which you use SPACE to go through doors.

     At the start of each mission,your boss (Mac Halpin) will explain to
     you what's going on.Then,before each level you will be told:

     1-THE LEVEL NAME:this is often quite irrelevant,and consists of the
       OASIS or THE WHO songs that I like,or was listening to while
       drawing that picture.

     2-OBJECTIVES:This is very important,since it is what you have to do
       in order to complete the level.Mostly,you have to reach the exit
       area (you'll be told where it is-usually at the far left of the
       level),but sometimes you are also required to kill all enemy within
       the level.In this case,if you arrive at the exit area and there are
       still baddies alive you won't be moved to the next level,until you
       have killed the remaining enemies.

     3-NOTES:some comments on the level background,etc

    You can skip lots of levels,but you have to find how first! ; )
    Look out for warning signs that tell you how to do it,or give clues
    about it!

    At the end of mission 2,you are told how to start the game at mission
    3.

    Now,something that you must understand is that secret rooms are a vital
    part of the game.You WILL NOT make it to the end if you don't find a
    couple of hidden extra lives.

    The secrets rooms are are usually behind walls that seem to be
    solid,when in fact they can be walked over,there are blocks which are
    actually ladders...I have said enough!!

