                             @{b}@{u} KNOWN BUGS @{ub}@{uu}

       Backbone is a great program,but it is not really suited for
       such a big project.The game is incredibly chip-memory hungry.
       That means that during play,the game might freeze.I said MIGHT.
       I know for sure that if you play the game WITHOUT reading any warning
       signs,it is much less likely to lock up.
       So,my advice is to read the warning signs only the first time
       around.

       Even though the game multitasks,and returns to WB (by pressing
       CTRL+C),you are strongly adviced to play it without running any
       background programs (IE booting without startup-sequence and
       executing it from here).

       If you want to be picky,you can point out that sometimes the
       animation of Charly shooting the shotgun is not 100 % accurate,but
       there was no way in which I could have done it better.Sorry!

       Oh,I am sure that there must be some spelling mistakes.My native
       language is Spanish,remember.So please let me know if you find any!


       If you come across something nasty,then please @{"contact me"  link
       "Emilio Perez"}

