                           @{b}@{u} SOME TIPS @{ub}@{uu}


       1-Read carefully what you are supposed to do before each mission
         begins.You usually don't have to kill everything.That means that
         there is no point chasing someone if you are not required to kill
         all enemy,and not to mention if you are wielding a pistol or
         other small weapon.

       2-It is often impossible to kill an enemy the first time he charges
         at you.The best thing to do is shoot him two or three times,then
         jump over him,and when you land quickly turn around and shoot
         him from behind.This depends on the weapon you are wielding,too.
         For example,the tuaregs can be killed in one go with the pistol
         the first time around if you hold down FIRE as soon as you spot
         them running towards you.They will kick the bucket just in
         front of you.
         The snakes that are found in the desert levels can be killed by
         jumping over them,too.
         Oh,and be careful-later on enemy use to follow you around,rather
         than roam from right to left!

       3-Enemy that shoots at you WILL NOT hurt you if you touch him-only his
         bullets will.This is VERY important.

       4-It does not pay to be fancy.


