                    Look...A secret bit on the docs!WOW!

                        Has anybody done this before?


   Here you have a small guide to the game...

   The pistol,machine gun and shotgun are the weapons you'll see most often.
   The shotgun is the pick of this bunch.Then you have the "big" weapons:
   the launcher,the flamer and the special weapon.The launcher can be found
   in most levels-always pick it up.The flamer is usually hidden,as is the
   Special Weapon,which is the best weapon in the game.
   In mission 3 you pick up a sword and shurikens.The sword is the worst
   weapon in the game.Only pick it up to get used to it,since the boss
   on this mission involves a sword duel.The shuriken is the
   second best weapon in the game.To get it,you have to kill the special
   brown ninja that faces you at the end of levels 2 and 3.

   Remember,the key to success is not to run like mad around the levels-
   always go carefully,and when and enemy charges towards you,jump over
   him (if you have a small weapon) or quickly shoot him,if you have a
   big weapon (IE launcher).

   You WON'T make it to the end if you don't find any hidden extra lives.
   Not only you get the lives-they are usually in company of a big weapon.

   Mission 1:It is made of 6 levels.Levels 1 and 2 can be skipped.Look out
   for clouds which are solid and can therefore be walked over.
   Level 5 has got a shortcut,which is revealed to you during mission 2
   level 1.
   On level 6,it may be worth picking up the pistol at the start,since it
   can be shot while jumping,and that would definitely be helpful.

   Mission 2:It is made of 5 levels.Levels 2 and 3 can be skipped.

   Mission 3:Made of 5 levels.Only level 1 can be skipped.This is when the
   game starts getting harder.

   Mission 4:Made of 4 sections.7 levels in total.Levels 1 and 2 can be
   skipped.This is very hard-make sure you have a fair amount of lives.
   Many can be found during this mission,though.At the end of the first
   level you can pick a life and a launcher,which would prove vital.
   Section 2 is full of doors.Personally speaking,I would take the first
   one.There is a flamer besides the second one.
   Section 3 greets you with the most dangerous enemy of the whole game,
   besides the crusher.It is a flying homer armed with a laser,and it is
   very tough.It takes 4 shotgun bursts to kick the bucket.It may be a
   good idea not to face it unless you have one of the "big" weapons.
   Section 4 is a big melee.Try to pick the enemies one by one.Usually,
   if you run away they'll follow you and you'll end up in further trouble.
   The final boss of the game is not as hard as it seems.First of all,
   get the launcher (top left of the level) or the flamer (left,near the
   starting point).If you have 6 or more lives,simply stand besides it and
   hold down the fire button.Don't worry about the guardian's shoots as
   they only take one energy point away.Try to dodge the boss itself shoots,
   that take a lot more.Whatever you do,be careful not to touch the boss,
   since you will automatically lose a life.


   Oh,and if you thought this was an excellent game,just you wait and see the
   sequel...THAT would be excellent.This is just very good,in my personal
   opinion,though is a very important step forward for me.

   Thanks for everything.


